quran[202]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,Successful indeed are the believers (or the believers will eventually win)
  23,2,Who in their prayers are humble
  23,3,And who shun vain talk
  23,4,And who are constantly active in charitable works
  23,5,And who abstain from sexual immodesty (or guard their modesty or chastity or sexual purity)
  23,6,"Except for with those joined with them in marriage or the captive whom their right hand possesses, for then, verily, they are free from blame"
  23,7,"But whoever craves aught beyond that, they are the transgressors"
  23,8,And those who faithfully observe their trusts and covenants
  23,9,And who guard well (pay heed to) their prayers
  23,10,These will be the heirs
  23,11,Who shall inherit Paradise; they shall dwell therein
  23,12,We have created man from an extract of clay
  23,13,Then We made him a drop (sperm) in a safe depository (the womb)
  23,14,"Then We made the drop into a clot, and We made the clot into a lump (foetus); then We made the lump into bone, and We clothed the bone with flesh; then We produced from it another creature. Blessed be Allah, the best of Creators"
  23,15,Then shall you after that surely die
  23,16,"Then, lo! On the Day of Resurrection shall you surely be raised"
  23,17,And We have created above you seven paths; and We are never heedless of creation
  23,18,"And We send down from the heaven water by measure, and We make it rest in the earth; but, verily, We are able to withdraw it"
  23,19,"Then We produce for you thereby gardens of date-palms and grapes wherein you have much fruits, and whereof you eat"
  23,20,"And a tree growing out of Mount Sinai (Olives) which produces oil, and a relish for eaters"
  23,21,"And, verily, you have a lesson in the cattle; We give you to drink of what is in their bodies; and you have therein many uses, and of them you eat"
  23,22,And on them and on ships you are carried
  23,23,"We sent Noah unto his people, and he said, \"O my people! Serve Allah, you have no God but Him; do you then not fear (evil)"
  23,24,"Said the chiefs of those who disbelieved among his people, \"This is nothing but a mortal like yourselves who wishes to make himself superior to you. Had Allah pleased He could surely have sent angels. We have not heard of this from our forefathers"
  23,25,He is nothing but a man possessed; so watch him for a while
  23,26,"Said he, \"My Lord! Help me, for they deny me"
  23,27,"And We inspired him, saying \"Make the ark under Our eyes and Our inspiration; and when the oven (of Allah´s wrath) boils over (or the fountains or springs of the earth are about to gush forth), conduct into it of every kind two spouses, and you"
  23,28,"But when you are settled, you and those with you in the ark, say, \"Praise belongs to Allah, Who saved us from the unjust people"
  23,29,"And say, ´My Lord! Cause me to land on a blessed landing place, for you are the best of all who bring to land.´"
  23,30,"Verily, in this is a sign, and, verily, We are ever trying them (mankind)"
  23,31,Then We raised up after them another generation
  23,32,"And We sent amongst them a messenger of their own (or from among them), saying, \"Serve Allah, you have no God but He; will you then not fear (evil)"
  23,33,"Said the chiefs of the people who disbelieved, and denied the meeting in the Hereafter, and to whom We gave enjoyment in the life of this world, \"This is only a mortal like yourselves, who eats of what you eat, and drinks of what you drink"
  23,34,"If you obey a mortal like yourselves, verily, you will then be surely losers"
  23,35,"Does he promise you that when you are dead, and have become dust and bones, that then you will be brought forth"
  23,36,"Be gone, be gone, with that which you are promised (or it is far-fetched)"
  23,37,"There is only our life in this world. We die and we live, and we shall not be raised again"
  23,38,He is only a man who invents a lie about Allah. And we believe him not
  23,39,"Said he, \"My Lord! Help me, for they deny me"
  23,40,"He said, \"Within a little while they will surely be sorry"
  23,41,"Then the blast seized them rightfully; and We made them as rubbish borne by a torrent (of Time); so, away with the wrong-doing people"
  23,42,Then after them We brought forth other generations
  23,43,"No nation (or people) can hasten its appointed term, nor delay it"
  23,44,Then We sent Our messengers one after another. Whenever its messenger came unto any nation they denied him; so We caused them to follow one another (to disaster); and We made them bywords. Away then with a people who believe not
  23,45,"Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron with Our signs, and with plain authority"
  23,46,"To Pharaoh and his chiefs, but they were inflated with pride, and were a despotic people"
  23,47,"And they said, \"Shall we believe two mortals like ourselves, and whose people are servile unto us"
  23,48,"So they accused them of lying, and became of those who perished"
  23,49,"And We verily gave Moses the Book, that per chance (or possibly) they might be guided"
  23,50,"And We made the son of Mary and his mother a sign; and We gave them both shelter on high, a place of security and springs"
  23,51,"O you messengers! Eat of the good things and do right; verily, I am aware of what you do"
  23,52,"And, verily, this your religion (or brotherhood) is one religion (or brotherhood), and I am your Lord; so keep your duty unto Me"
  23,53,"But they (mankind) have broken their religion (or affair) between them into sects, each sect rejoicing in its own tenets"
  23,54,So leave them in their confused error (or ignorance) for a time
  23,55,"Think they that in the wealth and children, wherewith We provide them"
  23,56,"We hasten unto them with good things? Nay, but they perceive not"
  23,57,"Verily, those who walk in awe of their Lord"
  23,58,And those who believe in the revelations of their Lord
  23,59,And those who ascribe not partners unto their Lord
  23,60,And those who give what they give with heart afraid because they are about to return unto their Lord
  23,61,"These race to good things, and they shall be the first in the race"
  23,62,"But We will not oblige a soul beyond its capacity; for with us is a Record that utters the truth, and they shall not be wronged"
  23,63,"Nay, their heart are in ignorance of this, and they do deeds beside this which they continue to do"
  23,64,"Until, when We catch the affluent ones amongst them with the punishment, then lo! They cry in supplication"
  23,65,"Supplicate not this day! Assuredly, you will not be helped by (or against) Us"
  23,66,"My revelations were recited to you, but you turned back upon your heels"
  23,67,"In arrogant scorn thereof, raving vain nonsensical tales by night"
  23,68,"Have they not pondered over the words, or has something new come unto them which came not to their forefathers"
  23,69,Or know they not their messenger that they thus deny him
  23,70,"Or do they say, \"He is possessed\"? Nay, but he came to them with the Truth, and most of them are haters of Truth"
  23,71,"But if the truth were to conform to their desires, verily, the heavens and the earth and whoever is therein would be corrupted. Nay, We brought them their Reminder (The Quran), but from their Reminder they now turn away"
  23,72,"Or do you ask them for a tribute? But the bounty of your Lord is better, for He is the best of those who provide"
  23,73,"And, verily, you do call them to the Straight Way"
  23,74,"But, verily, those who believe not in the Hereafter, they are indeed astray from that Way"
  23,75,"But if We had mercy on them, and relieved their distress, they still would persist in their rebellion, blindly wandering on"
  23,76,"And We caught them with the punishment, but they humble not themselves before their Lord, nor do they pray"
  23,77,"Until, when We open for them the gate of extreme torment, then lo! They are plunged into despair"
  23,78,"He it is who produced for you hearing and sight, and heart (or feelings, understanding, mind). Little thanks give you"
  23,79,"And He it is Who has sown you broadcast in the earth, and unto Him shall you be gathered"
  23,80,And He it is Who gives you life and death; and His is the alternation of the night and the day; have you then no sense
  23,81,"Nay, but they say the like of that which those of yore did say"
  23,82,"They said, \"What! When we have become earth and bones, are we then going to be raised again"
  23,83,"We were already promised this, we and our forefathers. Lo! this is naught but old folks´ tales"
  23,84,"Say, \"Whose is the earth and those who are therein, if you have knowledge"
  23,85,"They will say, \"Allah´s.\" Say, \"Will you then not remember"
  23,86,"Say, \"Who is Lord of the seven heavens, and Lord of the Mighty Throne"
  23,87,"They will say, \"Allah.\" Say, \"Will you then not keep your duty unto Him"
  23,88,"Say, \"In whose hand is the dominion over all things; He succours (or protects) but is not succoured (or needs no protection or against whom there is no protection), if you did but know"
  23,89,"They will say, \"Allah´s\". Say, \"How then can you be so deluded"
  23,90,"Nay, We have brought them the Truth, but, verily, they are Liars"
  23,91,"Allah never took a son, nor was there ever any God with Him; else would each God have assuredly gone off with (or championed, controlled) that which he had created, and some would assuredly have exalted themselves over (or overcome) others. Glorified be A"
  23,92,"Knower of the invisible and the visible, exalted be He above what they associate with Him"
  23,93,"Say, \"My Lord! if you should show me what they are promised"
  23,94,My Lord! Then place me not amongst the wrong-doing people
  23,95,And verily We are able to show you that which We have promised them
  23,96,Repel evil by that which is best. We are best Aware of that which they allege
  23,97,"And say, \"My Lord! I seek refuge in Thee from the suggestions of the devils"
  23,98,And I seek refuge in Thee from their presence
  23,99,"Until when death comes to any one of them he says, \"My Lord! Send me back"
  23,100,"That I may do right in that which I have left behind.\" Nay! It is but a mere word he speaks; behind them is a barrier until the Day they shall be raised"
  23,101,"And when the trumpet shall be blown, and there shall be no kinship between them on that day, nor will they ask about each other then"
  23,102,"And those whose scales are heavy (with good deeds), they are the successful"
  23,103,"But those whose scales are light, these are they who lose their souls, in hell will they abide"
  23,104,"The fire shall scorch their faces, and they shall curl their lips (in gloom) therein"
  23,105,"(It will be said) \"Were not My revelations recited to you? And did you not treat them as falsehoods"
  23,106,"They will say, \"Our Lord our misfortune overcame us, and we became a people astray"
  23,107,"Our Lord! Take us out of this, and if we return to evil, then shall we be unjust indeed"
  23,108,"He will say, \"Be gone into it, and speak you not to Me"
  23,109,"Verily, there was a sect of My servants who used to pray, \"Our Lord! We believe, so forgive us, and have mercy upon us, for Thou art the best of the merciful ones"
  23,110,But you took them for a jest (treated them with ridicule) until you forgot My reminder and did laugh at them
  23,111,"Verily, I have rewarded them this day that they were steadfast; verily, they are indeed triumphant, blissful now"
  23,112,"He will say, \"How long a number of years did you tarry on earth"
  23,113,"They will say, \"We tarried but a day or part of a day, but ask those who keep count"
  23,114,"He will say, \"You have only tarried a little, if you but knew"
  23,115,"Did you then think that We created you for jest (or sport, without purpose), and that you would not be returned to Us"
  23,116,"But exalted be Allah, the True King; there is no God but He, the Lord of the Noble Throne (or Throne of Honour)"
  23,117,"He who calls unto any other God along with Allah has no proof thereof; verily, his account is only with his Lord; verily, the disbelievers shall not be successful"
  23,118,"And say, \"Lord, Forgive and have mercy, for you are the best of the merciful ones"
  24,1,This is a chapter which We have revealed and ordained. In it We have revealed manifest signs in order that you may take heed
  24,2,"The man and the woman guilty of adultery (fornication, whoring), scourge each of them with a hundred stripes, and let not compassion for them withhold you from obedience to Allah, if you believe in Allah and the Last Day; and let a party of the believers"
  24,3,"Let no adulterer marry any but an adulteress or an idolatress (or unbeliever), nor let any but such a man or an idolater (or unbeliever) marry such a woman. All this is forbidden to believers"
  24,4,"And those who launch a charge (accusations, imputations) on chaste women, but bring not four witnesses, scourge them with eighty stripes, and never afterwards accept their testimony, for these are, indeed, evil-doers (workers of abomination)"
  24,5,"Except such as repent after that and make amends, for, verily, Allah is Forgiving and Merciful"
  24,6,"And those who cast charges (accusations, imputations) against their wives and have no witnesses except themselves, then the testimony of one of them shall be to testify four times that, by Allah, he is of those who speak the truth"
  24,7,"And a fifth, to invoke the curse of Allah on him if he be of those who lie"
  24,8,"And it shall avert the punishment from her if she bears testimony four times that, by Allah, he is of those who lie"
  24,9,And the fifth that the wrath of Allah shall be on her if he be of those who speak the truth
  24,10,"And were it not for the grace of Allah upon you and His mercy unto you, and that Allah is Relenting, Wise (he would have been ruined)"
  24,11,"Verily, those who spread the slander are a gang among you. Deem it not as an evil for you. Nay, it is good for you. Every man of them shall have what he has earned of sin; and he among them who had the greater share (took the lead), for him is an awful do"
  24,12,"Why did not, when you heard it, the believers, men and women, think good of their own folk, and say, \"This is an obvious lie"
  24,13,"Why did they not bring four witnesses to it? But since they did not bring witnesses, then verily they stand forth as liars in the sight of Allah"
  24,14,"And but for the grace of Allah upon you, and His mercy in this world and the Hereafter, an awful doom would have seized you, for that which you glibly and hastily spread abroad"
  24,15,"Behold, you received it with your tongues, and spoke with your mouths what you had no knowledge of, and deemed it a light thing, while it was most grave in the sight of Allah"
  24,16,"And why, when you heard it, did you not say, \"It is not for us to speak of this? Glory be to Thee, O Allah, this is an awful slander"
  24,17,"Allah admonishes you that you return not to the like of it ever, if you be believers"
  24,18,"And He expounds to you His revelations, for Allah is Knower, Wise"
  24,19,"Verily, those who love to see slander (or scandal) broadcast amongst the believers, for them is grievous woe in this world and the Hereafter; Allah knows, but you know not"
  24,20,"And but for the grace of Allah upon you, and His mercy, and that Allah is kind and compassionate"
  24,21,"O you who believe! Follow not the footsteps of Satan, for he who follows the footsteps of Satan, verily, he bids you filth (the shameful) and wrong. Had it not been for the grace of Allah upon you and His mercy unto you, not one of you would have grown pu"
  24,22,"And let not those amongst you who have plenty (dignity and ease and ample means) swear that they will not give aught to their kinsman and the needy and those who are fugitives from their homes in the cause of Allah, but let them forgive and show indulgenc"
  24,23,"Verily, those who slander (cast aspersions) on virtuous (or chaste) women who have been careless (indiscreet) but believing, shall be cursed in this world and the Hereafter; theirs will be an awful doom"
  24,24,On the day when their tongues and hands and feet shall testify against them as to what they used to do
  24,25,"On that day Allah will pay them their just due; and they shall know that Allah, He is the Manifest Truth"
  24,26,"Vile (impure) women are for vile (impure) men, and vile men for vile women. Good women are for good men, and good men for good women, such are innocent of what people they say; for them is forgiveness and a noble provision"
  24,27,"O you who believe! Enter not into houses which are not your own, until you have asked permission (announced your presence) and saluted (invoked peace on) the people thereof. That is better for you; per chance (or possibly) you may be mindful"
  24,28,"And if you find no one therein, then enter not until permission is given you, and if it be said unto you, \"Go away.\" then go away, for it is purer for you; Allah knows what you do"
  24,29,"It is no crime against you that you enter uninhabited houses, wherein is comfort for you; but Allah knows what you proclaim and what you hide"
  24,30,"Say to the believing men that they cast down their looks and guard their modesty; that is purer for them; verily, Allah is well aware of what they do"
  24,31,"And say to the believing women that they cast down their looks and guard their modesty, and display not their ornaments, except those which are obvious from the outside; and let them pull their veils over their bosoms and not display their ornaments (and beauty) save to their husbands and fathers, or the fathers of their husbands, or their sons, or the sons of their husbands, or their brothers, or their brothers´ sons, or their sisters´ sons, or their women, or what their right hands possess (slaves), or their male attendants who are incapable (eunuchs or old men), or to children who do not note women´s nakedness; and that they beat not with their feet to draw attention to their hidden ornaments; but turn you all to Allah, O you believers, in order that you may succeed (or prosper or attain bliss)"
  24,32,"And marry the single amongst you, and the righteous among your slaves and your handmaidens. If they be poor, Allah will enrich them of His grace, for Allah encompasses all and knows all"
  24,33,"And let those who cannot find a match keep chaste until Allah gives them means from His grace. And if any of your slaves asks for a Deed in writing (an agreement to purchase their freedom), write it for them if you know any good in them; yea, give them so"
  24,34,"Now have We sent down to you clear revelations, and the example of those who have passed away before you, and as an admonition to those who fear (avoid) evil"
  24,35,"Allah is the light of the heavens and the earth; The similitude of His light is as a niche in which is a lamp, and the lamp is in a glass, the glass is as though it were a brilliant star; it is lit from a blessed tree, an olive neither of the east nor of"
  24,36,"(This lamp is found, or the light is lit) In the houses which Allah has permitted to be exalted and that His name shall be remembered (or mentioned) therein. His praises are celebrated therein mornings and evenings"
  24,37,"By men whom neither merchandise nor selling (commerce) divert from the remembrance of Allah and steadfastness in prayer and charity, who are in awe of the day when heart and eyes shall be transformed"
  24,38,"That Allah may reward them for the best of that which they have done, and give them increase of His bounty; for Allah gives blessings without stint to whom He will"
  24,39,"But those who disbelieve, their works are like the mirage in a desert, the thirsty suppose it to be water till when he comes to it he finds nothing, but he finds, instead, Allah is with him; and He will pay him his account, for Allah is quick to take acco"
  24,40,"Or like darkness on a deep sea. There covers it a wave above which is another wave, above which is a cloud, layers of darkness upon darkness; when he puts out his hand he can scarcely see it; for him to whom Allah has given no light, he has no light"
  24,41,"Have you not seen that Allah, He it is whom praise all who are in the heavens and the earth, and the birds in their flight? Each one knows its worship and its praise, and Allah is aware of what they do"
  24,42,"And unto Allah belongs the sovereignty of the heavens and the earth, and unto Allah is the journeying"
  24,43,"Have you not seen how Allah drives the clouds gently, and then gathers them together, then heaps them up (or layers them)? Then you may see the rain coming forth from their midst; and He sends down from the sky mountainous masses wherein is hail; He smite"
  24,44,"Allah alternates the night and the day. Verily, in all these things is a lesson to those endowed with vision"
  24,45,"And Allah created every beast from water, and of them are some that creep upon their bellies, and some that walk upon two legs, and some walk upon four. Allah creates what He wills; verily, Allah has power over all things"
  24,46,"We have, indeed, sent down revelations which make things (hidden) manifest, and Allah guides whom He pleases unto the Straight Way"
  24,47,"They say, \"We believe in Allah and in the Messenger, and we obey.\" But after that some of them turn their backs; they are not really believers"
  24,48,"And when they appeal to Allah and His Messenger to judge between them, lo! A section of them is averse"
  24,49,But had the right been on their side they would have come unto Him willingly enough
  24,50,"Is there in their heart a disease, or do they doubt, or do they fear lest Allah and His Messenger should deal unjustly by them?- Nay, it is they who do wrong (or are unjust)"
  24,51,"The speech of the believers, when they appeal unto Allah and His Messenger to judge between them, is only to say, \"We hear and we obey;\" and such are the successful"
  24,52,"He who obeys Allah and His Messenger and fears Allah and keeps his duty to Him, such indeed are the victorious"
  24,53,"They swear by Allah with their most solemn oath that had you ordered them they would surely go forth. Say, \"Swear not; obedience is more reasonable; verily, Allah is Informed of what you do"
  24,54,"Say, \"Obey Allah and obey the Messenger; but if you turn away then it is for him to do only that wherewith he has been charged, and for you to do only that wherewith you have been charged. If you obey him, you are rightly guided. But the Messenger ha"
  24,55,"Allah promises those of you who believe and do right that He will give them the succession (or make them inheritors to the present rulers), in the earth even as He gave the succession to those before them; and that He will surely establish for them their"
  24,56,"Establish regular worship and regularly pay the Zakah (the poor-tax) and obey the Messenger, in order that you may obtain mercy"
  24,57,"Think not that those who disbelieve can frustrate (the plan of Allah) on earth; their resort is the Fire, and it is indeed an ill destination"
  24,58,"O you who believe! Let those whom your right hands possess (slaves), and the children amongst you who have not reached puberty, ask leave of you on three occasions (before coming into your presence) - before the prayer of dawn, and when you put off your c"
  24,59,"And when your children reach puberty let them ask leave as those before them asked leave. Thus does Allah explain to you His revelations, for Allah is Knower, Wise"
  24,60,"And women past childbearing, who have no hope of marriage, it is no crime for them if they discard their outer garments in such a way as not to display their adornments. But to refrain is better for them, for Allah is Hearer, Knower"
  24,61,"There is no blame upon the blind, nor blame upon the lame, nor blame upon the sick nor on yourselves if you eat from your houses, or the houses of your fathers, or the houses of your mothers, or the houses of your brothers, or the houses of your sisters"
  24,62,"Only those are believers who believe in Allah and His Messenger, and when they are with him (the Messenger) upon some common business, go not away until they have asked leave of him. Verily, those who ask your leave they it is who believe in Allah and His"
  24,63,"Make not the calling (or summons) of the Messenger among you like your calling (or summons) one to the other. Allah knows those of you who steal away, hiding themselves. And let those who conspire to evade his orders beware lest grief or painful punishmen"
  24,64,"Verily, to Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth. He knows their condition, and the Day when they shall be returned unto Him so that He may inform them of what they did. Allah is Knower of all things"
  25,1,Blessed is He Who has revealed unto His servants the Discrimination (or Criterion) that it may be an admonition to all peoples
  25,2,"He unto Whom belongs the sovereignty of the heavens and the earth, He has chosen no son nor has He any partner in the sovereignty. He has created everything, and then given it its measure (proportions)"
  25,3,"Yet they take beside Him other gods who create not aught, but are themselves created, and cannot control harm or profit for themselves, and can control neither death, nor life, nor resurrection"
  25,4,"And those who disbelieve say, \"This is nothing but a lie which he has invented, and another people hath helped him with it;\" But, in truth, it is they who have wrought an injustice and a falsehood"
  25,5,"And they say, \"Old folks´ tales, which he has written down while they are dictated to him morning and evening"
  25,6,"Say, \"He Who knows the secret of the heavens and the earth, He has revealed it; verily, He is ever Forgiving, Merciful"
  25,7,"And they say, \"What ails this messenger that he eats food and walks in the markets? Why is not an angel sent down unto him, to be a Warner with him"
  25,8,"Or a treasure thrown down unto him, or why has he not a garden to eat from....?\" And the unjust say, \"You only follow a man bewitched (or obsessed)"
  25,9,"See how they coin similitudes for you, so that they are all astray and cannot find a way"
  25,10,"Blessed is He Who, if He will, can make for you better than all that - Gardens beneath which rivers flow - and can make for you castles (mansions, palaces)"
  25,11,"Nay, but they deny the coming of the Hour, and for those who deny the Hour We have prepared a blaze"
  25,12,"When it sees them from a far place, they shall hear its raging and roaring"
  25,13,"And when they are thrown into a narrow place thereof, chained together, they shall pray for destruction there"
  25,14,"Pray not that day for one destruction, but pray for many destructions"
  25,15,"Say, \"Is that better or the Garden of Eternity (Immortality) which is promised unto those who fear (ward off evil), which is ever a reward and a goal"
  25,16,"Therein abiding, they shall have all that they desire. It is for your Lord a promise that must be fulfiled"
  25,17,"And on the day when He will gather them and that which they served beside Allah, He will say, \"Was it you who misled these my servants or did they themselves wander from the way"
  25,18,"They will say, \"Be you glorified! It was not befitting for us to take any patrons besides Thee; but Thou didst give them and their fathers ease until they forgot the Reminder and became a lost people"
  25,19,"And thus have they proved you liars for what you say, and you cannot avert or obtain help. And he among you who does wrong, We will make him taste great torment"
  25,20,"We have not sent before you any messengers, but lo! They ate food and walked in the markets; but We have made some of you a test for others: will you be steadfast? your Lord is ever Seer"